[1]Egbert (c. 950 - 9 December 993) was the Archbishop of Trier from 977 to its mortEncyclop√©die catholic.Egbert is the son of Thierry II, count of Holland.
[2]After his education at Egmond and the court of Brunon of Cologne, he became the chancellor of Otto II in 976.
[3]The following year he was appointed archbishop of Trier.
[4]In 984, he joined the conspiracy of Henry II of Bavaria against Otto, but returned to camp the following year.Egbert was a boss, renamed the arts and sciences.
[5]He oversaw himself the creation of the Registrum Gregorii.
[6]He was also the dedicatee of the Codex Egberti, without doubt, composed at Reichenau.
[7]However, Trier became from of its mandate, the rival of the Reichenau as an artistic centre of the world ottonien.
